Package hr.fer.zemris.java.custom.collections

Class LinkedListIndexedCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • hr.fer.zemris.java.custom.collections.Collection
      • hr.fer.zemris.java.custom.collections.LinkedListIndexedCollection

  • public class LinkedListIndexedCollection
extends Collection
    Linked list backed collection of elements with list node containing pointer to the next and previous element (double linked list). Duplicate elements are allowed in the list, storage of null references is not allowed.
    Author:
    Dorian Ivankovic

        public void insert​(java.lang.Object value,
                   int position)
        Insert the given value at the specified position in linked-list, but does not replace the element at position but shifts all elements starting from position one place to the right. The average complexity of this method is O(n/4)
        Parameters:
        value - - value to add in the collection
        position - - position in which to insert value
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if value is null
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if position is < 0 or > size
